{How do you think does Black needs to organyze the defense or not? Try to
figure out where and how Black needs to place and replace his pieces. Black's
turn.} 1... Ne8 {Black puts the Knight to e8 with an idea to defend e5 pawn
with f6 and Knight is a perfect defender for g7 square. Also after White's
idea of playing f4 and taking on e5, Black can take with d pawn and then bring
this Knight on a perfect square d6.} 2. f4 {A clear idea to open the center
and attack Black on the king-side.} Bd8 {A very nice defensive move, whic is
all about the chapter Economy in defense. Black relocate this bishop to active
b6 square and prepare 7th rank for the Rooks, if it will be necessery to
defend it.} 3. Kh2 {Nice move which doesn't allow Black to exchange of dark
squared bishops after Bb6.} Qc8 {Preparing the idea of Bb6.} 4. Qe2 {With this
move White connects the Rooks and prepare attack on thhe black King!} Bb6 5.
Rf1 {The idea is to bring the Rook in the attack on the black King with move
Rf1 - f3 - g3.} f6 {A very nice defensive move, it defends the pawn on e5 and
clear 7 rank for rooks.} 6. Nh5 Qd8 7. Rf3 Bc8 {Again a very nice defensive
move, which follows the idea of clearing 7 rank.} 8. Rg3 Kh8 9. f5 {White
closes the center and takes some space on the king-side.} Ra7 {Rook finaly
gets to be on the 7 rank and perfectly defends black King and the g7 square.}
10. Nf3 Nd7 {One more defensive move, Knight wants to go on f8 and Black wants
also to exchange darksquared Bishop.} 11. Bd2 {White can not allow this
exchange to happen, becouse without darksquared Bishop White doesn't have
enough pieces for the attack.} Nf8 12. Nh4 Qe7 {You can see how nice Black
plays in this position. Black has exactly enough pieces in the defense and
White can not make any progress in the attack, and on the other hand, Black
can with this economic defense use the rest of his piesec for achieveing the
progress on the queen-side with the moves like b4 and so on.} *

