{White is on the move and he plays Re4! Great attacking move! What do you
think? Is White much better? Can White mate black King or Black has enough
resources for the defense? How do you think, in which way Black needs to
defend? Where does he need to put his pieces?} 1. Re4 {It seems like White has
a strong attack on the black King. All of the White's pieces attack black King.
But if you look at it carefully, you will see that Black is also defending
himself with all pieces he needs. After Re4 idea is to bring the Rook to the h
file and the Knight on g5 and the Queen to h5.} Nce7 {Economic defense! Knight
from c6 comes to defense!} 2. Nxd5 Nxd5 3. Rh4 g6 {A nice move that does not
allow White's Queen to get to the h5 square and Black does not need to bring
his perfect Knight from d5 to defense on f6 if there is no need to do this.} 4.
Rxc8 Qxc8 5. Ng5 {Now White wants to take the h7 pawn.} Be7 {A great defensive
move. There is no need to play h5 and potentially allowing White to sacrfice
some piece on h5.} 6. Qg4 {White wants to bring the Queen to h3 and attack h7
pawn once again.} h5 {Now this is the tempo. Black doesn't not alow White to
take on h7 and makes White get his Queen from g4.} 7. Qg3 Qb8 {Now once again
you can see perfect economic defense. Black defends himself only with the
pieces that he needs. After of the excahnge of the Queens White will not have
any attacking chances and all of his pieces will be on the wrong side of the
board.} *

