{What do you think Black needs to play here? White wants to attack Black with
f4. Can the black Knight stay on e5? And what is the future of this Knight?
Where do you think Black needs to move this knight?And how to organyze some
counter-chances? Black's turn.} 1... Nd7 {This is a very nice defensive move!
Black wants to transfer the Knight to f8, from where it will defend the
potentially endangered h7 square.} 2. Rad1 a5 {Nice move. Black wants to get
this Bishop from the attacking b3 square and also maybe later on to play Ra5.}
3. c3 a4 4. Bc2 {White tries to relocate the Bishop to c2 and with next move
Qh3 to attack h7 square.} Re8 {Nice move. Rook plays great role on the half
open e file and removes from f8 square, allowing the Bishop or the Knight to
move there.} 5. Qh3 {Now you can see the point. White wants to attack the h7
square.} Nf8 {And the Knight is on f8. The Knight is perfectly placed. This
piece defends the vital h7 square and secure the black King. Black defend
himself very economically. Only with the Knight on f8.} 6. Be3 Qa5 7. a3 Qb5 {
One more perfect move following the idea of the economic defense. Black use
only the Knight for the defense and all other pieces for the counter-play.} *

